name: MarsMoonVenus
description:
Taken the evening of July 11, 2021 in the desert of Twentynine Palms, California. The sky is almost completely clear at night, and you can see not only the waxing crescent of the moon, but the outline of the entire surface. The bright dot to the left of the moon is the planet Mars and to its left, the faint sign of the planet Venus.

All artist proceeds for this image go toward supporting NiftyFilm.io, the only resource on the internet dedicated to educating and empowering independent filmmakers to take full advantage of the power of NFTs to disseminate their work, build an audience, and foster community.
